{{Infobox person | name = Marita Grabiak | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!--{{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = [[Ambridge, Pennsylvania|Ambridge]], [[Pennsylvania]], U.S.<ref>[http://www.filmreference.com/film/1/Marita-Grabiak.html Marita Grabiak Biography at FilmReference.com]</ref> | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = | occupation = Television director | years_active = 1986–present | spouse = }}
'''Marita Jane Grabiak''' (born in [[Ambridge, Pennsylvania|Ambridge]], [[Pennsylvania]]) is an American [[television director]]. She began her career as a production assistant on the film ''The Men's Club'' (1986) along with fellow Joss Whedon collaborator Tim Minear.<ref>{{cite book|last=Barton|first=Kristin|title=The Big Damn Firefly & Serenity Trivia Book|year=2011|publisher=BearManor Media|isbn=978-1-59393-681-5|pages=1}}</ref> She has directed episodes of several television series including ''[[Dawson's Creek]]'', ''[[Dollhouse (TV series)|Dollhouse]]'', ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'', ''[[Firefly (TV series)|Firefly]]'', ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[Angel (1999 TV series)|Angel]]'', ''[[Smallville]]'', ''[[Cold Case]]'', ''[[Gilmore Girls]]'', ''[[Everwood]]'', ''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]'', ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'', ''[[The Inside (TV series)|The Inside]]'', ''[[Alias (TV series)|Alias]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'', ''[[Point Pleasant (TV series)|Point Pleasant]]'', ''[[One Tree Hill (TV series)|One Tree Hill]]'', and most recently, ''[[American Horror Story]]''.<ref>[http://www.maritagrabiak.com/resume.pdf Marita Grabiak's resume] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714034803/http://www.maritagrabiak.com/resume.pdf |date=2011-07-14 }}</ref><ref>http://maritagrabiak.com/media/maritagrabiak_resume2016.pdf</ref>
She is a graduate of [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]].<ref>[http://www.maritagrabiak.com/resume.html Marita Grabiak's biography at official website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714034813/http://www.maritagrabiak.com/resume.html |date=2011-07-14 }}</ref>
