{{Infobox journal | title = n.paradoxa | cover = [[File:N.paradoxa cover.jpg|180px]] | editor = [[Katy Deepwell]] | abbreviation = n.paradoxa | discipline = [[Art criticism]], [[feminist art]], [[art history]], [[art theory]] | publisher = KT press | frequency = Biannual | history = 1996–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.ktpress.co.uk/ | link2 = http://www.ktpress.co.uk/nparadoxa-issue-details.asp | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 40759869 | LCCN = sn99017107 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1461-0434 | eISSN =1461-0426 }} '''''n.paradoxa: international feminist art journal''''' is an [[academic journal]] covering [[feminist art criticism]] and the work of [[women artists]] since the 1970s.<ref name=Deepwell2002>{{cite journal |last=Connor |first=Maureen |title=Working Notes: Conversation with Katy Deepwell |journal=Art Journal |date=2002 |volume=61 |issue=2 |pages=32–43 |url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00043249.2002.10792116#.U7unRUCmW2U |doi=10.2307/778180}}</ref> It is published by KT press and the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Katy Deepwell]] (London).<ref name=Krikos2004>{{cite book |last1=Krikos |first1=Linda A. |last2=Ingold |first2=Cindy |title=Women's Studies: A Recommended Bibliography |date=2004 |publisher=Libraries Unlimited |location=Westport, Conn. |isbn=1563085666 |page=726 |edition=3rd}}</ref>
The current print journal (printed as volumes, {{ISSN|1461-0434}}) was established by Deepwell in 1998. Prior to this, ''n.paradoxa'' existed as an [[electronic journal|online journal]] (issues 1-21, {{ISSN|1461-0426}}) which was established in 1996 and this parallel edition online ran until 2010 with entirely different content to the print journal.<ref name=ADRC>{{cite web |title=n.paradoxa: international feminist art journal |url=http://adri.mdx.ac.uk.contentcurator.net/n-paradoxa-international-feminist-art-journal |publisher=Art and Design Research Centre, Middlesex University |accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Rampley |first=Matthew |title=Art History and Visual Studies in Europe: Transnational Discourses and National Frameworks |date=2012 |publisher=Brill Academic |location=Leiden |isbn=9004218777 |pages=360–361}}</ref> Each volume of ''n.paradoxa'' focuses on a particular theme and typically includes articles devoted to [[feminist aesthetics|art theory]] and criticism from a [[feminism|feminist]] perspective,<ref>{{cite web |title=Cloud List of countries in articles from n.paradoxa: international feminist art journal |url=http://www.ktpress.co.uk/search-articles.asp |publisher=KT press |accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> as well as interviews with artists.<ref name=Krikos2004/> The website contains extensive online resources on feminism in the visual arts internationally, including reviews of exhibits, books, and websites.<ref name=nparadoxa>{{cite web |title=Cloud List of countries in book resources of n.paradoxa: international feminist art journal |url=http://www.ktpress.co.uk/feminist-art-books.asp |publisher=KT press |accessdate=8 July 2014}}</ref> The journal is published biannually in January and July. ''n.paradoxa'' participated in the [[Documenta 12 magazines]] project as part of the 2007 [[documenta]] exhibition in [[Kassel]]. After 2011, volumes were simultaneously published in print and electronic format online, both with {{ISSN|1461-0434}}.
