[[File:Play instrument THATTAI.jpg|thumbnail|Thattai]]

The '''thattai''' is an Indian percussion instrument, belonging to the [[idiophone]] instruments family. It consists in a cane tube, in which the end has three reeds (two of them free) that produce a percussive sound when the shaft is shaken with one hand. Thattai is used as a toy or as rhythmic accompaniment instrument.

